 ### 3. Test if all type-hints are correct
+#### Run Black
+
+
+
+We use [Black](https://github.com/psf/black) as our code formatter.
+Black will automatically format your code to conform to PEP 8 standards with a line length of 100 characters.
+To help with that, we encourage you to install the git pre-commit hook that will automatically format your code on commit.
+
+You can manually run Black with `black .` to format all Python files in the repository.
+
+##### Black configuration
+
+* Line length: 100 characters
+* Black is configured to exclude certain directories (vendor, build, dist, etc.) as specified in pyproject.toml
+
 
